column2: Taxonomic Serial Number - a unique, persistent, non-intelligent identifier for a scientific name in the context of the Integrated Taxonomic Information System (ITIS).

Biological Condition Gradient (BCG) taxa attribute assignments (1i, 1m, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6). 1i = sensitive specialist or regionally endemic; 1m = moderately tolerant specialist or regionally endemic; 2 = highly sensitive; 3 = sensitive ubiquitous; 4 = moderately tolerant; 5 = highly tolerant; 6 = nonnative
